{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline"],"title":"Essentials","generated":true}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Anatomy of a Game","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/anatomyofagame"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How a single Swift type becomes a world the engine can run."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A Gnusto game is one type conforming to ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","isActive":true},{"text":". That one type carries everything: the rooms and things, where they start, and the rules that govern them. This article covers the model underneath — how the engine finds your declarations, how one value is both a declaration and a live reference, and how the immutable world is kept separate from the state that changes as the player plays.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once that model is clear, the rest of Gnusto follows from it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Declarations are stored properties","anchor":"Declarations-are-stored-properties","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rooms, things, and custom state are declared as ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"stored properties"}]},{"text":" of the game type:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct OperaHouse: Game {","    let foyer = Location { name(\"Foyer of the Opera House\") }","    let bar   = Location { name(\"Foyer Bar\"); dark }","    let cloak = Item { name(\"velvet cloak\"); wearable }","    @Global var disturbances = 0","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you construct the world with ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameWorld\/init(game:)","isActive":true},{"text":", the engine’s bootstrap reflects over the game value with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Mirror"},{"text":" and collects every ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","isActive":true},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","isActive":true},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","isActive":true},{"text":". It names each entity after the property it was stored in: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foyer"},{"text":" becomes ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"foyer\""},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cloak"},{"text":" becomes ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"cloak\""},{"text":", and so on. You never write these IDs by hand — the property name ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"is"}]},{"text":" the name.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is why declarations must live in the type’s main body, not an extension: Swift only allows stored properties there, and the Mirror only sees stored properties. (When even the declarations need to span files or ship separately, that is what a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","isActive":true},{"text":" bundle is for — see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","isActive":true},{"text":".)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"One value, two roles","anchor":"One-value-two-roles","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A declaration and a live reference are the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"same value"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let cloak = Item { name(\"velvet cloak\"); wearable }   \/\/ the declaration","","\/\/ …later, inside a rule body:","cloak.after(.take) {","    if cloak.isWorn { … }        \/\/ the live reference — reads current state","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cloak"},{"text":" is an ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","isActive":true},{"text":" value. Written in the game body it ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"declares"}]},{"text":" the cloak. Used in a rule it ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reads and writes the live cloak’s state"}]},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/isWorn","isActive":true},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/isHeld","isActive":true},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/name","isActive":true},{"text":", and so on all consult the current turn.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This works because each ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","isActive":true},{"text":" mints a private identity token when it is created. The token — not the struct’s contents — is the entity’s identity, and it survives copying. Two items are equal when they share a token (","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/==(_:_:)","isActive":true},{"text":"). Inside a turn, the token resolves to the entity’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","isActive":true},{"text":" and then to its state; outside a turn there is no state to read, so a live property access traps with an explanation rather than returning a meaningless value.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"References are always compile-checked. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cloak.after(.take)"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hook.holds(cloak)"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foyer.north(bar)"},{"text":" — every one is ordinary property access, so renaming a room or deleting an item breaks the build instead of the running game.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"The parts of the `Game` protocol","anchor":"The-parts-of-the-Game-protocol","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","isActive":true},{"text":" gathers a handful of members, most with defaults so a small game declares only what it needs:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"title"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"intro"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tagline"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"maxScore"},{"type":"text","text":" — the banner and scoring metadata."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":" — geography and initial placement, as a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Read once at startup to build the initial state."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" — all game logic, as a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" value. Defaults to empty."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" — player-typeable verbs this game adds, as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[SyntaxRule]"},{"type":"text","text":". Defaults to empty. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":" — content bundles the game composes itself from, as "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Defaults to empty. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The protocol extension also hands every game three ambient references usable as bare identifiers inside ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":" blocks:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"player"},{"type":"text","text":" — the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Player","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", for its location, score, and inventory."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"world"},{"type":"text","text":" — the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", for rules that apply everywhere (like daemons)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"command"},{"type":"text","text":" — the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Command","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" currently being performed, inside a rule body."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"The `map` block","anchor":"The-map-block","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" is a result-builder property that yields a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap","isActive":true},{"text":" — a flat list of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/MapEntry","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" statements: exits, blocked exits, initial item placements, and the player’s start."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["var map: WorldMap {","    foyer.south(bar)                 \/\/ an exit","    foyer.north(blocked: \"Not yet.\") \/\/ a blocked exit with a refusal message","    bar.north(foyer)","","    player.starts(in: foyer)         \/\/ where the player begins","    cloak.startsWorn                 \/\/ where each thing begins","    hook.starts(in: cloakroom)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Exits are directional and one-way: "},{"code":"foyer.south(bar)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" does not imply "},{"code":"bar.north(foyer)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Declaring both is deliberate, so asymmetric maps (a chute, a one-way door) need no special case. Because "},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a builder, you can split it across files and compose it from sub-maps — see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Immutable definition, mutable state","anchor":"Immutable-definition-mutable-state","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Internally, the engine keeps two things strictly apart:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"definition","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is everything that never changes during play: names, descriptions, exits, rules, and the parser’s vocabulary. It is built once, from your declarations, at startup."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"state"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" is everything that ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"does","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" change: where each item is, what is lit, the score, the turn count, which things have been touched, and your "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global"},{"type":"text","text":" values."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The entire mutable state is a single ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"text":" value. That is a deliberate design choice: because all change funnels through one value, a turn’s mutations can be committed atomically at its end (see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"), and save\/restore becomes a serialization call rather than a feature bolted across the codebase."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you write "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cloak.isWorn"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"player.score += 1"},{"type":"text","text":" in a rule, you are reading and writing that one state value through the entity’s token — never touching the definition, and never seeing another turn’s half-finished changes."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"See also","anchor":"See-also","level":2},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item/isHeld":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/isHeld","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"isHeld","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isHeld"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"True if the player is carrying the item (including worn items)."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item\/isheld"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/MapEntry":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"One statement in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" block: an exit, a blocked exit, an initial item","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"placement, or the player’s starting location.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MapEntry","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MapEn